{
  "texts": [
    "Students can also hover over a static correct block to check the number of blocks missing above and below it in the relative location (Fig. 1.B).In a partially movable Parsons puzzle, there are also paired distractor sets.",
    "Each pair consists of two blocks connected with a purple edge and an \"or\" (Fig. 1.C).",
    "For the two movable code blocks in one paired distractor set, only one code block is necessary for the correct solution.",
    "In CodeTailor, the distractor code block is either created using the student's incorrectly written code (Fig. 2B-P2) or generated using an LLM from the student's correctly written code (Fig.",
    "When solving the personalized Parsons puzzles in CodeTailor, students can use the \"Check\" button to check their answer and receive block-based feedback that highlights the incorrect blocks (Fig. 1.G)."
  ]
}